docs.abstract: On the eve of the state funeral for former President George Bush, the men and women who helped him run the nation gathered in Washington for reunion of sorts.
docs.snippet: On the eve of the state funeral for former President George Bush, the men and women who helped him run the nation gathered in Washington for reunion of sorts.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Jonathan Bush had just left a lunch and was about to head over to the Capitol to visit his brother’s coffin. By evening, he planned to stop by a reception for the extended Bush circle. Everywhere he went, he was reuniting with many of the old gang.

headline.main: ‘A Mixture of Sad and Joyful’: The Old Bush Gang Gathers for a Final Send-Off
headline.print_headline: ‘Mixture of Sad and Joyful’ As Family Comes Together

docs.abstract: Some of the nation’s largest businesses asked Senator Cindy Hyde-Smith to return campaign donations after she said she would attend a “public hanging.” She is not complying.
docs.snippet: Some of the nation’s largest businesses asked Senator Cindy Hyde-Smith to return campaign donations after she said she would attend a “public hanging.” She is not complying.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When video surfaced last month of Senator Cindy Hyde-Smith of Mississippi telling a supporter she would be “on the front row” if he invited her to a “public hanging,” some of the country’s largest corporations found themselves in a public relations nightmare.

headline.main: Companies Asked a Mississippi Senator to Refund Donations. They Are Still Waiting.

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve continues to raise interest rates, prompting concerns that growth will slow — and workers will reap fewer of the benefits.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve continues to raise interest rates, prompting concerns that growth will slow — and workers will reap fewer of the benefits.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump renewed his attacks on the Federal Reserve on Monday in a tweet expressing incredulity that the Fed continues to raise interest rates. While his outbursts have drawn widespread criticism for being impolitic, a growing number of experts think the president has a point.

headline.main: Higher Interest Rates Could Lighten Workers’ Wallets
headline.print_headline: Some Economists Say Trump Has a Point on Interest Rates

docs.abstract: The investigation must be completed “in less than a week,” the president said, bowing to a request from Senate Republican leaders facing an insurrection in their ranks.
docs.snippet: The investigation must be completed “in less than a week,” the president said, bowing to a request from Senate Republican leaders facing an insurrection in their ranks.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, ceding to a request from Senate Republican leaders facing an insurrection in their ranks, ordered the F.B.I. on Friday to reopen a background investigation of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh, his nominee to the Supreme Court, and examine the allegations of sexual assault that have been made against him.

headline.main: Trump Agrees to Open ‘Limited’ F.B.I. Investigation Into Accusations Against Kavanaugh
headline.print_headline: President Orders a ‘Limited’ Inquiry Into Kavanaugh

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos and Sheryl Gay Stolberg

docs.abstract: Using an array of accounts on multiple platforms and targeting a variety of demographics, the Russians have generated millions of interactions with their posts.
docs.snippet: Using an array of accounts on multiple platforms and targeting a variety of demographics, the Russians have generated millions of interactions with their posts.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Russia targets Americans on social media, it has political goals: in 2016, to damage Hillary Clinton and help elect Donald J. Trump; since then, to press Russian views on issues like the conflicts in Syria and Ukraine; and in the future — who knows?

headline.main: Some of the Popular Images and Themes the Russians Posted on Social Media

docs.abstract: Federal prosecutors in New York and Washington are examining whether people from several Middle Eastern countries used straw donors to obscure donations to the funds.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal prosecutors are examining whether foreigners illegally funneled donations to President Trump’s inaugural committee and a pro-Trump super PAC in hopes of buying influence over American policy, according to people familiar with the inquiry.

headline.main: Trump Inaugural Fund and Super PAC Said to Be Scrutinized for Illegal Foreign Donations
headline.print_headline: Inquiry Shifts To Committees Tied to Trump

docs.abstract: The former governor of New Jersey said he was not offered the job but had met with President Trump and had a good discussion.
docs.snippet: The former governor of New Jersey said he was not offered the job but had met with President Trump and had a good discussion.
docs.lead_paragraph: Chris Christie, the former governor of New Jersey, took himself out of the running for the job of White House chief of staff on Friday, the latest person to decline a chance to replace John F. Kelly as President Trump’s highest-ranking aide.

headline.main: Chris Christie Drops Out of Consideration for White House Chief of Staff
headline.print_headline: Christie Drops Out of Race For Chief of Staff Position

docs.abstract: The president again dismissed the campaign violations that his former lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, is accused of committing at his behest and said they were civil violations at best.
docs.snippet: The president again dismissed the campaign violations that his former lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, is accused of committing at his behest and said they were civil violations at best.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Thursday that if there was anything illegal about the hush payments made to two women claiming to have had affairs with him, it was the fault of his former lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, part of a newly improvised attempt to combat the legal exposure the president may now have because of the payments.

headline.main: Trump Improvises New Defense in Hush Money Payments
headline.print_headline: Trump Blames Cohen: ‘He Is Supposed to Know the Law’

byline.original: By Maggie Haberman and Michael S. Schmidt

docs.abstract: Mr. Webb’s views align closely with President Trump’s drive to pull American troops from the Middle East and confront China more aggressively.
docs.snippet: Mr. Webb’s views align closely with President Trump’s drive to pull American troops from the Middle East and confront China more aggressively.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is considering Jim Webb, a former Democratic senator and Reagan-era secretary of the Navy, to be the next defense secretary, according to three officials, potentially bypassing more hawkish Republicans whose names have been floated to replace Jim Mattis.

headline.main: White House Mulls Jim Webb, Ex-Democratic Senator, as Next Defense Secretary
headline.print_headline: Critic of Iraq War Eyed to Replace Mattis

docs.abstract: By absenting himself, the Senate majority leader had hoped to push the blame for a prolonged shutdown onto Democrats while protecting Republicans running for re-election next year — including himself.
docs.snippet: By absenting himself, the Senate majority leader had hoped to push the blame for a prolonged shutdown onto Democrats while protecting Republicans running for re-election next year — including himself.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For weeks, Senator Mitch McConnell, the Republican leader, has remained conspicuously on the sidelines, insisting that it was up to President Trump and Democrats to negotiate an end to the partial shutdown of the federal government.

headline.main: McConnell Faces Pressure From Republicans to Stop Avoiding Shutdown Fight
headline.print_headline: Pressure Building on McConnell to Get More Engaged

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Nicholas Fandos
